Stixbox Function

NAME

    df - The F density function

CALLING SEQUENCE

f = df(x,df1,df2)

PARAMETERS

    • x : real (scalar, vector or matrix)
    • d :f1,df2 degrees of freedom
    • f : F density function at the value of x, of (X/df1)/(Y/df2) where X and Y are independent Chi-square variables with one degree of freedom

DESCRIPTION

    The F density function (or Fisher-Snedecor density function)
